 {"id":"bd-j9wwn","title":"add mounted-path btrfs create-and-mkdir under non-directory parent ENOTDIR coverage","description":"Survey finding: btrfs mounted-path FUSE E2E proves create and mkdir success, but the public ENOTDIR refusal for create/mkdir beneath a regular-file parent is still only covered in ffs-core unit tests. Scope: add btrfs mounted-path probes that attempt file creation and mkdir beneath a non-directory parent and assert exact ENOTDIR with no partial directory mutation. Acceptance: fuse_e2e freezes btrfs create/mkdir non-directory-parent refusal behavior.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T09:14:37.637632908Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T23:58:11.342939040Z","closed_at":"2026-04-21T23:58:11.340438978Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
